22 section shall be prominently displayed in the registrar's office or absentee ballot clerk's
23 office."
24 SECTION 2.
25 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 21-2-409.1, relating to voting by
26 electors who are 75 years of age or older or disabled electors without having to wait in line,
27 as follows:
28 "21-2-409.1.
29 On election day between the hours of 9:30 A.M. and 4:30 P.M., each elector who is 75
30 years of age or older, who is accompanied by one or more children two years of age or
31 younger, or who is disabled and requires assistance in voting as authorized by Code
32 Section 21-2-409, shall, upon request to a poll officer, be authorized at any primary or
33 election to vote immediately at the next available voting compartment or booth without
34 having to wait in line. Notice of the provisions of this Code section shall be prominently
35 displayed in the voting place."
36 SECTION 3.
37 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
